This paper discusses the design of electronic interfaces for publishers and their impact on usage statistics, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely category is cs.DL (Digital Libraries), followed by cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), as the paper focuses on user behavior and interface design in the context of electronic journals. The paper also touches on issues related to cybersecurity (cs.CR) and cyberinfrastructure (cs.CY), which are less directly related but still relevant to the topic.
